2.content:
Impact on First-Time Homebuyers 

Strict proof-of-funds requirements may discourage first-time buyers who are still learning about the market. Should they be locked out of viewings just because they haven’t finalized financing?

3.content:
Final Thoughts  

Requiring proof of funds before viewing is a double-edged sword. It helps filter serious buyers but can also feel intrusive and discourage potential clients.

God, and women, desire men to have consistency, decisiveness, and strength.

Strength is tested by resistance to pressure. True of marriage, friendships, character.

Every man has three men to deal with:

✨The man he thinks others see.

✨The man he thinks he is.

✨The man he really is.

11.content:
You cannot compensate by sacrifice what you lose through disobedience.

Maturity does not come with age, but begins with the acceptance of responsibility.

12.content:
Every man is limited by three things:

✨The knowledge in his mind.

✨The strength of his character.

✨The principle upon which he is building his life.

Use it to your advantage.

Your mind is powerful, it's up to you to use it.

- Pursuing understanding

You can't prove this externally.

6.content:
Teaching writing is messy.

It rarely goes well.

Clarity of thought must be earned.

Earned by reading, thinking, writing, editing, quitting, beginning again, and believing.

Believing that within the mess, an idea, a concept, a realization can bloom.

7.content:
Instead of cluttering whiteboards with standards and objectives, teachers should focus on deeply engaging with the text they’re teaching.

Reading it three or more times allows you to internalize it—when you truly feel the text, your teaching naturally improves.

8.content:
This is a great time of the school year to make adjustments.

-Experiment with a new seating chart.
-Alter the bathroom policy.
-Focus on smoother transitions between tasks.

These small adjustments make a giant difference over time.

42.content:
The "Walk and Write" approach to writing a 1-hour essay.

- Go for a walk with students.
- Students write for 20 mins.

- Go for another walk.
- Write for 20 mins.

- Go for another walk.
- Write for 20 minutes.

Fresh ideas often come after the walk.

6.content:
Teaching writing is messy.

It rarely goes well.

Clarity of thought must be earned.

Earned by reading, thinking, writing, editing, quitting, beginning again, and believing.

Believing that within the mess, an idea, a concept, a realization can bloom.

7.content:
Instead of cluttering whiteboards with standards and objectives, teachers should focus on deeply engaging with the text they’re teaching.

Reading it three or more times allows you to internalize it—when you truly feel the text, your teaching naturally improves.

8.content:
This is a great time of the school year to make adjustments.

-Experiment with a new seating chart.
-Alter the bathroom policy.
-Focus on smoother transitions between tasks.

These small adjustments make a giant difference over time.

42.content:
The "Walk and Write" approach to writing a 1-hour essay.

- Go for a walk with students.
- Students write for 20 mins.

- Go for another walk.
- Write for 20 mins.

- Go for another walk.
- Write for 20 minutes.

Fresh ideas often come after the walk.
